id: pm-b3e9
title: Pre-install package-owned command names should hint the owning package install command
description: "2026-07-04 sandbox review: in a fresh workspace, pm completion/guide/templates fail with generic unknown-command guidance (examples: pm --help, pm activity --help). These names are known package-owned surfaces (pm-guide-shell, pm-templates); unknown-command guidance should map known first-party package command roots to a hint like: install with pm install guide-shell --project. Keeps never-block promise for the pre-install experience."
