body: "## Context\n2026-07-04 sandbox review: in a fresh workspace, `pm completion`, `pm guide`, `pm templates` fail with generic unknown-command guidance (suggesting pm --help / pm activity --help) even though these are known first-party package-owned command roots (pm-guide-shell, pm-templates). Pre-install UX breaks the never-block promise.\n\n## Approach\nMaintain a static map of first-party package-owned command roots → owning package alias (derivable from the bundled catalog, same source as pm-jqd2's alias matching). When unknown-command dispatch misses, check the map first and emit: \"command 'guide' is provided by the guide-shell package — install with: pm install guide-shell --project\".\n\n## Definition of done\nFresh workspace: every bundled package-owned root command name yields the owning install hint; unknown non-package names keep the current did-you-mean; hint catalog covered by spec (install-hint catalog was 4→16 in the 2026-07-04 review — reuse it)."
